H0.text: Reducing fluid friction is the way an open parachute increases air resistance when a skydiver jumps from a plane.

H1.text: Increasing surface area is what causes the open parachute to increase the air resistance when a skydiver jumps from a plane.

H2.text: Increasing terminal velocity is what the open parachute will increase the air resistance by when a skydiver jumps from a plane.

H3.text: Decreasing mass is the factor by which the open parachute will increase the air resistance when a skydiver jumps from a plane.
